Paper: hep-th/9609037

Date: 1996-09-03

Title: Gauge Independence of the Lagrangian Path Integral in a Higher-Order

FormalismAuthors: I.A. Batalin, K. Bering and P.H. Damgaard

Comments: 6 pages, LaTeX

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B389 (1996) 673-676

We propose a Lagrangian path integral based on gauge symmetries generated bya symmetric higher-order $\Delta$-operator, and demonstrate that this pathintegral is independent of the chosen gauge-fixing function. No explicit changeof variables in the functional integral is required to show this.